\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 How many years }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6496488\charrsid5787272 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 id you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Oh I lived there until I was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Where did you go to live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Oh - to Golgellan. To {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Arran Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Golgellan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 
So you were born in Golgellan and then you moved to another house in Golgellan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Yes. No, I was born on a farm. A farm three miles outside Golgellan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 What did you do after that in terms of moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 
Well I worked at home on the farm until I was about fourteen and obviously I was gong to school as well. And then I went to work on a neighbouring farm where my grandfather and grandmother lived. And two uncl
es and a sister - their sister. And I was there until I was about fifteen. And then I went to work on another farm which faced - or was opposite our farm but about one and a half miles away. Where a young couple had settled down to live and were going to 
b
ring up a family. The thing was that there they expected me to look after the children when they went out. What they call babysitting today, and I didn't like that job. I went away from there, well in fact - I ran away from there, I escaped. I went home, 
i
t was on a Saturday night. I remember it was on a Saturday night that I came home. And then my mother worried a lot because the first world war had started and she saw that I was coming to an age where I'd have to join the Army. And she worried or fretted
 
a lot because I'd left - left farming and she particularly wanted me to go and work on another farm. But I saw other boys the same age as me working in the forest cutting trees during the war as pit props and I was very - envious at the other boys who cou
l
d show a lot of money on a Saturday. And I didn't get about - five bob a week. So I made up my mind either to go in the army or to go to work in the Forestry, and I got a job in the Forestry. In Pen-maen-Pwl. And I was there 'til - well I was there 'til t
he war ended. But I did get one exemption during that time to - say I needn't join the Army. That was when I'd reached eighteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Do you remember why your family left the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Well my father had died and my grandfather had got old and - because 
of this hardship we weren't able to carry hon. And it wasn't a big farm, it was a very small farm. I'm sure it's not big enough today to keep a man at home. And because of - his age - my grandfather's - and because I'd got work outside the farm and I wasn
't very happy to go and work on the farm again they moved from the farm to live in the town of Golgellan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Where did you live after leaving Golgellan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 
Well - I lived in Golgellan 'til 1946. Only during that time I'd been working away a lot. I worked at one time or another in every county in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. After I finished in the Forestry I went to work for a firm of contractors, road contractors, Davis Brothers, Barmouth. And I worked for them for fifteen years and during that time and during that time I worked in every part of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I worked as a steamer driver and as a traction driver and also in a job that made new roads. And through the help of the contract manager of Davis Brothers I was made a general foreman and I worked in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10879085\charrsid5787272 Amman ford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 , Neath, Aberto
weth, Hammerford West, Denbigh, - Colwyn Bay and every other part, this firm made roads throughout Wales and I looked after men - workers - well - all my life after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 When did you come to live in Llan Ffestiniog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Oh well I went to work for -
 the County Council in 1935. That was in Golgellan. As a general foreman. And I got appointed as the divisional road surveyor to the F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14317491\charrsid5787272 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 estiniog area, or the northern division of the county. Some of the towns of Merionethshire in 1946 and I was with that work for twenty years, until I retired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 That's when you were living here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Yes. And I re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5921178 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 . I lost my first wife in 1964. And I re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5921178 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272  in 1967 and came to live in this house, Pant Glas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 None. There was only me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Well he was twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Oh - from the same area. From a neighbouring farm. And
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 And he was a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Yes. He was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Did he have any work before he became a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 
Yes, he used to work on the estate of Penlaen Ucha as a forester and as a handyman, a man to do different jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Did he do any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 No, no, nothing like that. He had a brothe
r who was a watchmaker, and I spent a lot of time with this uncle, seeing him mending and improving watches and clocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Do you ever remember your father being unemployed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Do you remember how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15282467 RP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Twenty-six years old I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6963386 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11955618\charrsid5787272 Where did she come from?
